%U A394684 629,661,691,726,760,797,832,867,905,942,982,1021,1064,1105,1145,1189,1230,1278,1322,1368,1414,1461,1511,1560,1610,1661,1710
%N A394684 Number of ordered pairs of integers (x,y) with 0 <= x <= y and x^2+y^2 < n^2.
%C A394684 This is the number of integer vectors <x,y> satisfying the following 0 <= x <= y and |<x,y>| < n; or equivalently, x*x + y*y < n*n.
%C A394684 Related to A051132, which gives the number of integer vectors inside a circle of radius n. This sequence only counts unique nonnegative sorted vectors and asymptotically approaches the corresponding value of A051132 divided by 8. The set of these vectors can be used in algorithms such as k-nearest-neighbor sampling and circle rasterization.
%o A394684 (PARI) a(n) = sum(y=0, n-1, sum(x=0, y, x^2+y^2 < n^2)) \\ _Jason Yuen_, Mar 29 2026
%Y A394684 Equals A036702 - A063014.
%Y A394684 Equals A036702(n-1) + A077768(n-1) for n>1.
%Y A394684 Cf. A051132, A228172, A000603, A000328.
%K A394684 nonn,easy
%O A394684 0,3
